The MIT License above applies to Dilemma's SOURCE CODE.

The DATA ARTIFACTS that Dilemma builds or distributes - the SQLite lookup
database, the trained model weights, the corpus-frequency tables, and the
lemma/form corpus-attestation databases - are DERIVED FROM third-party sources
and remain subject to their respective upstream licenses, not the MIT license.
The full list of those sources and their licenses is in the NOTICE file.

The build is openly licensed by default: NonCommercial sources are never
ingested. The PROIEL treebank (CC BY-NC-SA) and UD Perseus are dropped
entirely, the NonCommercial GLAUx texts and NonCommercial PTA files are
filtered out, and UD Perseus is replaced by the AGDT original (CC BY-SA).
Gorman (CC BY-SA 4.0) and Diorisis (CC BY 4.0) are kept. See NOTICE for the
full per-source list.
